1. First, update your manifest to disable the default WorkManager initialization:

```xml:app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml
<provider
 android:name="androidx.startup.InitializationProvider"
 android:authorities="${applicationId}.androidx-startup"
 android:exported="false"
 tools:node="merge">
 <meta-data
 android:name="androidx.work.WorkManagerInitializer"
 android:value="androidx.startup"
 tools:node="remove" />
</provider>
```

2. Then, update your TestAppModule to use WorkManagerTestInitHelper instead of direct initialization:

```kotlin:app/src/androidTest/java/com/phoenix/pillreminder/di/TestAppModule.kt
@Module
@TestInstallIn(
 components = [SingletonComponent::class],
 replaces = [AppModule::class]
)
object TestAppModule {
 // ... other providers ...

 @Provides
 @Singleton
 fun provideWorkManager(app: Application): WorkManager {
 val config = Configuration.Builder()
 .setMinimumLoggingLevel(android.util.Log.DEBUG)
 .setExecutor(SynchronousExecutor())
 .build()

 // Initialize WorkManager for testing
 WorkManagerTestInitHelper.initializeTestWorkManager(app, config)
 return WorkManager.getInstance(app)
 }

 // ... other providers ...
}
```

3. Create a custom test application:

```kotlin:app/src/androidTest/java/com/phoenix/pillreminder/HiltTestApplication.kt
package com.phoenix.pillreminder

import android.app.Application
import androidx.work.Configuration
import dagger.hilt.android.testing.HiltTestApplication

class CustomTestApplication : HiltTestApplication(), Configuration.Provider {
 override fun getWorkManagerConfiguration(): Configuration {
 return Configuration.Builder()
 .setMinimumLoggingLevel(android.util.Log.DEBUG)
 .build()
 }
}
```

4. Update your AndroidManifest.xml for tests:

```xml:app/src/androidTest/AndroidManifest.xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
 package="com.phoenix.pillreminder">
 <application android:name=".CustomTestApplication" />
</manifest>
```

These changes will:
1. Disable the default WorkManager initialization
2. Allow proper initialization in the test environment
3. Prevent the double initialization error
4. Use a test-specific configuration for WorkManager"},{"role":"user","content":"
