Note that:
1. Replace `your_desired_color` with an actual color resource from your `colors.xml`
2. You can also use a color directly (e.g., `#FFFFFF`) or a drawable resource instead of a color
3. If you want to support both light and dark themes, you can create different styles in `values` and `values-night` folders

Alternatively, if you want to set the background programmatically, you can do it this way:

```kotlin:app/src/main/java/com/phoenix/pillreminder/feature_alarms/presentation/fragments/MyMedicinesFragment.kt
 private fun showFilterMenu(){
